ings will become apparent.   IT Asset Management: A Pocket Survival Guide is a quick reference style guide, addressing such serious issues with a fresh and pragmatic approach. Aimed at IT professionals who have been tasked with putting in place Asset Management disciplines, it first provides a commonsense introduction to the key processes outlined in the Information Technology Infrastructure Library (ITIL®), before proceeding to explain the various milestones of an Asset Management project. It will guide the reader through: building a hardware asset listing managing software asset inventory effectively, so compliance with software licences is achieved how to get senior management buy-in how to define, enforce and control procedures to manage IT assets more effectively for maximum savings. Buy this pocket guide today and get your Asset Management project underway.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aBusiness enterprisesxComputer networksxManagement. 0aIndustrial management. 0aInformation technologyxManagement. 0aInvestments. 0aManagement information systems. 0aOptions (Finance). 7aCOMPUTERS / General.2bisacsh  aIT asset management.  aIT management.  aITAM.  aasset management.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz978184928294940uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9781849282932  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles